[Student "E"]
{[showcards W:H8 N:H6]

The bidding has been as shown. West's 2\H bid shows good \S support with at least 10 points.

Partner led the \H8, dummy played the \H6 

Play a small \H.

Partner's \H8 lead is a high spot card, either top-of-nothing, or a singleton or doubleton. He definitely does not have an honor, which means that East holds \H A Q J.

In other words, your \HK is dead in the water. BUT, if you play it to this trick you hand East three \H tricks, while if you play a low \H he can only get 2 winners in the suit.

The extra winner would permit East to discard 2 of dummy's \D losers, and this would give East the contract.}
[Play "W"]H8

